The paper presents a vision-based algorithm for mobile robot localization and mapping, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm uses a binocular vision system for landmark detection, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The algorithm also uses a particle filter and Kalman filter, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithm's performance using simulations and experiments, which involves machine learning and statistical analysis (cs.LG).
